author: Ivan A. Melnikov
commit_message:
Basic MIPS support

This commit adds MIPS_32 and MIPS_64 to the list of known
architectures and updates README.md.

This commit also adds a testcase based on Loonson 3A3000
system (MIPS 64 Little Endian) running Loongnix 7
(linux-based OS which once was a Fedora clone).

author: Ivan A. Melnikov
commit_message:
Support MIPS-specific fields for flags/features

In MIPS world they are called 'application-specific extensions' (ASEs),
and are often listed in 'ASEs implemented' field of /proc/cpuinfo.

author: Ivan A. Melnikov
commit_message:
BE-T1000 (Baikal-T) support

BE-T1000 (formerly known as Baikal-T1) is a MIPS-based SoC.
It has two P5600 (mips32r5 little endian) cores.

To support it, we add two additional quirks:
- allow to use ',' as decimal separator for frequency;
- extract 'brand_raw' from 'model' field of lscpu output.
